data.name: username
data.description: For US domestic use 10-digit number. For International numbers use full E.164 format. Examples: US: 5555555555 E.164: +1155555555555
Takes a username and password and returns json with the account's session key. A sessionkey lasts forever, so it is best to store the sessionkey and use it for future purposes.

body
data.description: The message body that you would like to send. This is a maximum of 160 ASCII characters or 140 Bytes.

data.name: contacts
data.description: This is the contact ID that is return from contact/list. A contact ID is also part of the return from message/send.

data.name: session
data.description: This is the sessionKey that is returned from user/login. sessionKeys do not expire. Because of this, it is recommended that you do a single user/login and then save the sessionKey locally for future web calls.
